Flashover

33
00:03:21,561 --> 00:03:23,195
Damn, Nick.

34
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:25,697
Is there any blood ?

35
00:03:26,031 --> 00:03:27,332
A little on the airbag.

36
00:03:27,566 --> 00:03:29,367
Yeah, it looks like
he just hit the sign.

37
00:03:29,402 --> 00:03:31,336
No animals down on the road.

38
00:03:31,471 --> 00:03:32,771
You hear anything on the radio ?

39
00:03:32,806 --> 00:03:33,939
Not yet.

40
00:03:33,973 --> 00:03:35,540
What about that uniform ?

41
00:03:35,575 --> 00:03:37,376
Nick was gone when he
arrived on the scene,

42
00:03:37,410 --> 00:03:39,378
and I told him it's on me.

43
00:03:40,212 --> 00:03:41,813
But why ditch the car ?

44
00:03:41,848 --> 00:03:43,682
Trying to duck a DUI ?

45
00:03:44,116 --> 00:03:46,218
Message he left was a
whole lot worse than that.

46
00:03:47,752 --> 00:03:49,121
You think he was serious ?

47
00:03:49,155 --> 00:03:51,857
I called him back five times,
and he won't answer his cell.

48
00:03:54,091 --> 00:03:55,827
I'll get it towed to my guy,

49
00:03:55,862 --> 00:03:56,864
have him...

50
00:03:57,365 --> 00:03:58,965
clean it up.

51
00:03:59,299 --> 00:04:01,934
What the boss don't know can't hurt him, you know ?

52
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,169
He's got enough problems.

53
00:04:04,204 --> 00:04:06,939
Well, at least till we figure out what
the hell's going on.

54
00:04:07,273 --> 00:04:09,241
- Will or Kat know ?
- No.

55
00:04:09,275 --> 00:04:10,676
Figured it's bad enough I got you

56
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:11,877
on the hook for this now, too.

57
00:04:12,411 --> 00:04:14,546
It's Nick, Lil.

58
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:16,448
I mean, they'd want to know.

59
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:19,318
I'll have them swing by his place,

60
00:04:19,352 --> 00:04:21,487
see if he turns up.

61
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,493
The guy's a mess.

62
00:04:29,028 --> 00:04:31,163
Yeah, he's been for a while now.

63
00:04:31,397 --> 00:04:33,365
Schmitty's is up the road.

64
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:35,833
He's probably headed
home from the bar.

65
00:04:35,968 --> 00:04:37,703
Big guy with a voice.
Right ?

66
00:04:38,537 --> 00:04:39,871
He in some kind of trouble ?

67
00:04:39,939 --> 00:04:41,473
What kind of condition
was he in ?

68
00:04:41,508 --> 00:04:43,709
Just so you know, I didn't
serve him more than three.

69
00:04:43,743 --> 00:04:46,011
Guy tops it off in the parking lot,
that's on him.

70
00:04:46,046 --> 00:04:47,512
Not trying to jam you up.

71
00:04:47,547 --> 00:04:48,747
Just tell us when he left.

72
00:04:48,781 --> 00:04:50,515
About an hour ago,
wits about him.

73
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:52,418
I'll cut off anybody,
cop or no cop.

74
00:04:52,452 --> 00:04:53,452
Yeah. Yeah, we got that.

75
00:04:53,486 --> 00:04:54,920
Sounds like he's become a regular.

76
00:04:54,954 --> 00:04:57,823
Every night this week,
knocking back the Manhattans.

77
00:04:57,857 --> 00:04:59,358
He get into it with
anyone at the bar ?

78
00:04:59,392 --> 00:05:00,661
Not tonight.

79
00:05:00,662 --> 00:05:02,462
Keeps to himself,
regulars know he's a cop.

80
00:05:02,495 --> 00:05:03,962
Wait. What do you mean,
not tonight ?

81
00:05:03,997 --> 00:05:06,198
Last week, some idiot came in
here shooting his mouth off.

82
00:05:06,232 --> 00:05:08,233
Me and Big Mac tossed him
before it got out of hand.

83
00:05:08,368 --> 00:05:09,601
This idiot got a name ?

84
00:05:09,636 --> 00:05:10,836
What'd he look like ?

85
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,604
I don't know. Just some guy.

86
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:14,273
White, medium build,
maybe thirties.

87
00:05:14,307 --> 00:05:15,474
What was it about ?

88
00:05:15,808 --> 00:05:17,009
Not sure,

89
00:05:17,143 --> 00:05:19,011
but the guy was sure
busted up about something.

90
00:05:19,545 --> 00:05:21,947
You happy with yourself, detective ?
Thought you should know.

91
00:05:21,981 --> 00:05:23,748
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
I got it, buddy, okay ?

92
00:05:23,783 --> 00:05:24,750
I tried to tell you,

93
00:05:24,784 --> 00:05:26,552
but you wouldn't listen!
My brother's gone,

94
00:05:26,586 --> 00:05:29,120
- and that's on you now.
- Know what, jackass ?

95
00:05:29,154 --> 00:05:30,188
I told you to hit the bricks.

96
00:05:30,222 --> 00:05:31,923
You're nothing but a drunk bum.

97
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,158
Mac, get him out of here.
How you can live with yourself ?

98
00:05:33,192 --> 00:05:34,760
What does that mean ?
You need to calm down.

99
00:05:34,794 --> 00:05:36,261
Come on ! Just relax, man.

100
00:05:36,296 --> 00:05:37,896
Just calm down. Just relax.

101
00:05:38,031 --> 00:05:39,899
I'm all right.

102
00:05:44,870 --> 00:05:46,338
I don't know what
the guy's beef was.

103
00:05:46,372 --> 00:05:47,573
Something about his brother.

104
00:05:47,607 --> 00:05:50,976
He blamed Vera,
felt he wronged him somehow ?

105
00:05:51,010 --> 00:05:53,112
Cop never bothered nobody,
so I gave the guy the boot.

106
00:05:53,146 --> 00:05:54,947
- Nick ever here with anybody ?
- Nah.

107
00:05:54,981 --> 00:05:56,248
Mostly just drinks alone.

108
00:05:56,582 --> 00:05:58,484
Last couple nights
in here looking over

109
00:05:58,518 --> 00:06:00,052
some old file photos.

110
00:06:00,086 --> 00:06:02,588
Photos ? What, like,
crime scene photos ?

111
00:06:02,622 --> 00:06:03,756
I don't know.

112
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:05,224
They were dark, hard to make out.

113
00:06:05,258 --> 00:06:06,691
Like something burnt up.

114
00:06:06,826 --> 00:06:09,061
Honestly, his line of work...

115
00:06:09,095 --> 00:06:11,163
I didn't want to ask.

116
00:06:11,897 --> 00:06:13,465
Key still works.

117
00:06:14,834 --> 00:06:16,935
Clearly the maid don't.

118
00:06:17,269 --> 00:06:18,971
God, just when you
think you know a guy.

119
00:06:19,005 --> 00:06:21,073
Oscar needs a Felix.

120
00:06:23,609 --> 00:06:25,844
Told me he passed his physical.

121
00:06:28,414 --> 00:06:30,415
Dude's a time bomb.

122
00:06:31,984 --> 00:06:33,852
It's worse than I thought.

123
00:06:33,886 --> 00:06:35,921
- What was her name again ?
- Julie.

124
00:06:35,955 --> 00:06:37,400
Split up years ago.

125
00:06:37,401 --> 00:06:39,401
Booze and pills
definitely do not mix

126
00:06:39,402 --> 00:06:41,102
with photos of the ex.

127
00:06:43,934 --> 00:06:46,069
- What do you got ?
- It's a crime scene photo.

128
00:06:47,103 --> 00:06:50,039
Something I saw Nick looking
at a few weeks back.

129
00:06:56,979 --> 00:06:58,380
What the hell ?

130
00:06:59,315 --> 00:07:00,683
Can't you see
I'm taking a table nap ?

131
00:07:00,717 --> 00:07:01,951
Been a lot of those lately.

132
00:07:01,985 --> 00:07:03,386
What do you got ?

133
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,822
Some other case.

134
00:07:08,225 --> 00:07:10,026
Arson photo.

135
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,361
Didn't recognize it at the time.

136
00:07:12,996 --> 00:07:15,064
J.D. Billingsley, 11/06.

137
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:18,067
But why bring home a
four-year-old arson case ?

138
00:07:18,601 --> 00:07:20,336
Might have something to do
with the guy at the bar.

139
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:22,739
- You remember this case ?
- No.

140
00:07:22,773 --> 00:07:24,941
But the fire marshal would.

141
00:07:24,976 --> 00:07:26,211
Billingsley.

142
00:07:26,512 --> 00:07:28,512
Oh, yeah, I remember.

143
00:07:28,745 --> 00:07:31,714
Double homicide, arson,
couple years back.

144
00:07:31,749 --> 00:07:32,882
You worked that with Nick, right ?

145
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:34,884
Yeah, that's right. What's going on ?

146
00:07:34,918 --> 00:07:35,985
He contact you ?

147
00:07:36,019 --> 00:07:37,487
Any reason the case might come up ?

148
00:07:37,521 --> 00:07:39,155
No. Any reason it should ?

149
00:07:39,189 --> 00:07:41,258
Tell us about the arson case, Ray.

150
00:07:41,292 --> 00:07:43,292
Row house over in Kensington.

151
00:07:44,127 --> 00:07:46,229
Incendiary, pretty open and shut.

152
00:07:46,263 --> 00:07:47,363
J.D. Billingey ?

153
00:07:47,397 --> 00:07:48,798
Joe don billingsley.

154
00:07:48,832 --> 00:07:51,701
Lit up his own place,
middle of the night.

155
00:07:51,735 --> 00:07:52,969
It was a double homicide ?

156
00:07:53,003 --> 00:07:54,237
His own two boys.

157
00:07:54,971 --> 00:07:58,042
Drunk bastard had
custody for the weekend.

158
00:08:01,878 --> 00:08:04,080
Looks like a bomb went off.

159
00:08:04,114 --> 00:08:05,581
Flashover.

160
00:08:05,616 --> 00:08:08,684
Simultaneous ignition of
all combustible material.

161
00:08:08,719 --> 00:08:09,919
Flashover.

162
00:08:10,253 --> 00:08:14,423
Smoke and gas layer
got trapped at the ceiling.

163
00:08:15,859 --> 00:08:18,861
At 1,100 degrees,
the whole room burst into flames.

164
00:08:19,796 --> 00:08:21,730
Father said he was
asleep on the couch.

165
00:08:21,764 --> 00:08:22,865
Yeah, he also said

166
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:24,901
he couldn't get to the
kids' room down the hall.

167
00:08:24,935 --> 00:08:26,803
Yeah, ran into a wall of flame.

168
00:08:26,837 --> 00:08:29,506
With no burns on his bare feet ?

169
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,274
Thought he ran out the front door.

170
00:08:31,309 --> 00:08:34,310
Yeah, just let in more oxygen,
fed the beast.

171
00:08:34,344 --> 00:08:36,479
Did you see the crazed
glass back there ?

172
00:08:36,513 --> 00:08:37,847
Puddle configurations ?

173
00:08:37,881 --> 00:08:39,615
Multiple points of origin.

174
00:08:39,649 --> 00:08:41,884
Burn marks on the
baseboards and walls.

175
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,953
Yeah, all the way down the hall.

176
00:08:44,288 --> 00:08:45,889
Seen hundreds of these.

177
00:08:46,023 --> 00:08:47,691
Most of them do it
for the insurance.

178
00:08:47,725 --> 00:08:50,693
- No. This place was a rental.
- Whatever.

179
00:08:50,928 --> 00:08:52,229
Fire this hot don't
occur without the use

180
00:08:52,263 --> 00:08:54,698
of an accelerant.

181
00:08:55,332 --> 00:08:56,699
What, lighter fluid ?

182
00:08:56,733 --> 00:08:59,902
Butane, propane, maybe gasoline.

183
00:09:00,136 --> 00:09:01,771
Same result.

184
00:09:01,805 --> 00:09:05,208
Got your pour patterns
on the floor right there.

185
00:09:06,877 --> 00:09:09,011
Under the beds.

186
00:09:10,314 --> 00:09:12,916
Son of a bitch burned
his own kids up.

187
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:15,484
Then ran out of the house.

188
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:20,323
Three and five, those boys.

189
00:09:20,357 --> 00:09:22,325
That one just about
tore everybody up.

190
00:09:22,359 --> 00:09:23,593
Including Nick ?

191
00:09:23,627 --> 00:09:25,495
Nick was going through
a divorce at the time.

192
00:09:25,529 --> 00:09:26,929
Rubbed him pretty raw.

193
00:09:26,964 --> 00:09:30,399
Sick bastard killed his
kids just to spite his ex.

194
00:09:30,433 --> 00:09:31,734
Nick put him away ?

195
00:09:31,768 --> 00:09:33,002
Billingsley got life.

196
00:09:33,036 --> 00:09:34,937
He's lucky he didn't
get the needle.

197
00:09:34,972 --> 00:09:37,540
He didn't have the decency
to take his own life.

198
00:09:37,574 --> 00:09:40,409
Any reason Nick would be
looking into that case again ?

199
00:09:40,444 --> 00:09:41,910
Never said nothing to me.

200
00:09:41,945 --> 00:09:44,747
You remember if this Joe Don had
a brother ? Maybe at the trial ?

201
00:09:44,781 --> 00:09:46,215
I'm sorry, I don't.

202
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,550
Is everything okay ?

203
00:09:48,084 --> 00:09:49,819
Well, you hear from him, ray,

204
00:09:49,853 --> 00:09:51,521
let us know.

205
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:58,294
Joe don billingsley,
convicted in '08.

206
00:09:58,429 --> 00:10:00,963
Arson, double homicide.

207
00:10:00,998 --> 00:10:02,332
Doing life up in rockford.

208
00:10:02,366 --> 00:10:03,834
Was. Till he caught a shiv

209
00:10:03,835 --> 00:10:05,235
last week in the yard.

210
00:10:05,269 --> 00:10:07,336
Bled out. Old Joe Don's gone.

211
00:10:07,371 --> 00:10:09,472
Could be the guy Nick meant,
got killed ?

212
00:10:09,506 --> 00:10:11,340
A loudmouth at the bar blamed Nick

213
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:12,608
for his brother's death.

214
00:10:12,643 --> 00:10:13,709
Younger brother, Travis.

215
00:10:13,744 --> 00:10:16,378
Popped twice for DUI,
resisting arrest.

216
00:10:16,412 --> 00:10:18,314
Well, now he's stalking Nick.

217
00:10:18,348 --> 00:10:20,282
He was fired from his
last job at Costco.

218
00:10:20,317 --> 00:10:22,418
We're trying to track
down a new work address.

219
00:10:22,452 --> 00:10:23,619
Travis.

220
00:10:23,653 --> 00:10:25,955
Looks dumb enough
to go after a cop.

221
00:10:37,937 --> 00:10:39,370
Morning, lieutenant.

222
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,573
Something wrong with
the air upstairs, Pat ?

223
00:10:41,607 --> 00:10:44,676
You know where detective
Vera is, John ?

224
00:10:46,210 --> 00:10:47,578
I guess I'm about to find out.

225
00:10:47,612 --> 00:10:49,580
Don't jerk me around.

226
00:10:49,614 --> 00:10:51,649
I know all about the
abandoned department vehicle

227
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:53,150
out on Conshohocken road.

228
00:10:53,285 --> 00:10:54,652
- Okay.
- I also know

229
00:10:54,687 --> 00:10:57,388
that one of your detectives
had it towed to a private garage.

230
00:10:57,722 --> 00:10:59,658
- One of my detectives ?
- Can't say I blame them.

231
00:10:59,692 --> 00:11:02,460
Damaged vehicle,
reeking of kentucky sour mash.

232
00:11:02,494 --> 00:11:03,561
Get to it, Pat.

233
00:11:03,595 --> 00:11:05,296
That's a $35,000 vehicle

234
00:11:05,330 --> 00:11:06,597
that belongs to the department.

235
00:11:06,632 --> 00:11:07,832
And I would like to get it back

236
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,834
Before the commissioner
gets wind of this.

237
00:11:10,068 --> 00:11:11,870
Good as new.

238
00:11:14,239 --> 00:11:15,606
I'll get right on it.

239
00:11:15,641 --> 00:11:18,409
As for detective Vera, I would
suggest you find out where he is

240
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:20,244
and just what the hell is going on

241
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:21,646
before the end of the working day.

242
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,515
Oh, I'll get to the bottom of it.

243
00:11:29,154 --> 00:11:30,755
Put your house in order, John...

244
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,757
or I'll do it for you.

245
00:11:39,263 --> 00:11:40,498
Travis Billingsley.

246
00:11:40,932 --> 00:11:43,301
Detective Valens, Rush.

247
00:11:43,535 --> 00:11:45,303
That supposed to impress me ?

248
00:11:45,337 --> 00:11:46,805
Supposed to jog your memory.

249
00:11:46,839 --> 00:11:48,573
Last time you saw
detective Nick Vera.

250
00:11:49,108 --> 00:11:50,708
Why ? Something happened to him ?

251
00:11:50,743 --> 00:11:51,910
Asked you a question, pal.

252
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:53,044
How you know detective vera?

253
00:11:53,078 --> 00:11:54,879
Oh, so now I'm supposed
to help the police ?

254
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,716
How's that for an
impression, jackass?

255
00:11:59,551 --> 00:12:00,851
In case you need my badge number.

256
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:02,520
This ain't a courtesy call, Travis.

257
00:12:02,554 --> 00:12:05,056
You got into a bar fight with
detective vera last week.

258
00:12:05,590 --> 00:12:07,057
That wasn't a fight.

259
00:12:07,092 --> 00:12:09,126
Just tracked him down to
let him know what he did.

260
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:10,061
Yeah, what'd he do ?

261
00:12:10,095 --> 00:12:12,196
He put my brother away,
got him killed.

262
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,598
Yeah, real sorry they
don't look kindly

