781
00:32:41,381 --> 00:32:42,649
that getting locked up

782
00:32:42,684 --> 00:32:45,251
was the best thing
that ever happened to my son.

783
00:32:46,654 --> 00:32:49,722
Which, I guess,
is my roundabout way of saying

784
00:32:50,356 --> 00:32:51,791
you were right.

785
00:32:53,093 --> 00:32:54,494
So, I'm going to return the favor.

786
00:32:54,528 --> 00:32:56,963
- Pat, it was a long time ago.
- When or if

787
00:32:56,997 --> 00:32:59,599
you get your detective back,

788
00:32:59,633 --> 00:33:01,968
I expect you to do the same.

789
00:33:04,271 --> 00:33:06,039
- Nick...
- Take him off line.

790
00:33:06,073 --> 00:33:07,407
Send him to psych services.

791
00:33:07,441 --> 00:33:10,143
If that doesn't work,
take away his badge.

792
00:33:11,412 --> 00:33:12,545
Take care of it, John.

793
00:33:12,580 --> 00:33:14,547
I realize now it's the only way.

794
00:33:19,453 --> 00:33:20,887
Yeah, okay, thanks.

795
00:33:20,921 --> 00:33:22,689
That was the fire station.
Said Nick was just there

796
00:33:22,723 --> 00:33:24,691
15 minutes ago.
Got into it with Crawford.

797
00:33:24,725 --> 00:33:26,159
- Fight ?
- Said it got pretty heated

798
00:33:26,193 --> 00:33:28,161
until some firemen jumped
in and Nick took off.

799
00:33:28,195 --> 00:33:29,662
All right, call Lil and Scotty.

800
00:33:29,697 --> 00:33:31,031
See if they can catch up to him.

801
00:33:31,065 --> 00:33:33,132
The balls on that
guy coming in here,

802
00:33:33,167 --> 00:33:35,301
going at me how I do my job!

803
00:33:35,336 --> 00:33:36,636
Who the hell's he think he is ?

804
00:33:36,670 --> 00:33:38,771
- Calm down, Ray.
- Don't tell me to calm down !

805
00:33:38,806 --> 00:33:42,007
How would you like it some fireman
marches into the PPD,

806
00:33:42,041 --> 00:33:44,110
saying you messed up a case ?

807
00:33:44,144 --> 00:33:45,879
He came at you about Billingsley ?

808
00:33:45,913 --> 00:33:48,281
Whatever! Son of a bitch!

809
00:33:48,315 --> 00:33:50,550
This about half hour ago?
He on foot?

810
00:33:50,584 --> 00:33:53,052
Hell if I know. Couple of the
guys tossed him out on his ear.

811
00:33:53,087 --> 00:33:55,154
He's lucky I didn't break his jaw!

812
00:33:55,189 --> 00:33:57,190
Yeah, all right, all right.
Just tell us what happened.

813
00:33:57,224 --> 00:34:00,093
I've been a fire marshal
before he was a beat cop.

814
00:34:00,127 --> 00:34:03,196
Don't tell me what's
arson and what ain't.

815
00:34:04,897 --> 00:34:06,297
Take a look at the file, Ray.

816
00:34:06,503 --> 00:34:08,112
There were electrical
problems in the house.

817
00:34:08,113 --> 00:34:09,913
No residue of a
petroleum-based accelerant.

818
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:11,480
You're out of your freaking mind.

819
00:34:12,216 --> 00:34:13,641
Just take a look at
the file, please.

820
00:34:13,666 --> 00:34:14,650
Heard about enough.

821
00:34:14,845 --> 00:34:15,885
Get the hell out of here.

822
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:19,113
- I don't think he did it, Ray.
- I don't really care what you think.

823
00:34:19,137 --> 00:34:20,595
I know it's arson,

824
00:34:20,720 --> 00:34:22,892
just like you know a
murder when you see it.

825
00:34:23,017 --> 00:34:25,036
He never gave it up !
That never bothered you ?

826
00:34:25,104 --> 00:34:26,337
What are you talking about ?

827
00:34:26,365 --> 00:34:28,397
48 hours in the box,
I never got him to give it up.

828
00:34:28,522 --> 00:34:30,065
I always maintained his innocence.

829
00:34:30,190 --> 00:34:32,900
- That don't bother you ?
- No, that's between him and God.

830
00:34:34,088 --> 00:34:35,571
I went on what you told me, Ray.

831
00:34:35,696 --> 00:34:38,307
- That it had to be arson.
- What are you saying, that I'm wrong, Nick ?

832
00:34:38,535 --> 00:34:40,661
- That this is all on me ?
- No, no, I'm not saying that.

833
00:34:40,829 --> 00:34:42,993
Don't forget, you took
the witness statements.

834
00:34:43,118 --> 00:34:46,140
You testified on the stand
to his state of mind.

835
00:34:46,265 --> 00:34:46,896
Ain't denying that.

836
00:34:47,021 --> 00:34:48,572
The guy was a drunk !

837
00:34:48,697 --> 00:34:50,247
He's a terrible husband !

838
00:34:50,372 --> 00:34:52,488
Pissed off at his wife,
at the world.

839
00:34:52,613 --> 00:34:54,523
Been there
all those things, myself.

840
00:34:54,648 --> 00:34:56,225
It doesn't mean that
he killed his kids.

841
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:58,193
Oh, cry me a river.

842
00:34:58,218 --> 00:35:00,262
Joe Don Billingsley didn't
deserve what happened !

843
00:35:00,387 --> 00:35:03,522
- He didn't deserve to die !
- Boo-hoo! Live with it.

844
00:35:04,209 --> 00:35:05,768
We gotta make this right somehow.

845
00:35:05,893 --> 00:35:07,203
There is nothing to fix.

846
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:08,813
Guy's dead and gone.

847
00:35:09,518 --> 00:35:12,999
His ex-wife still thinks
that he killed her kids.

848
00:35:13,124 --> 00:35:15,679
His own parents think that
he killed their grandkids !

849
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:16,780
Guess what ?

850
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,047
So do I.

851
00:35:18,172 --> 00:35:20,173
And that's the way it's gonna stay.

852
00:35:21,313 --> 00:35:22,751
You do what you got to do !

853
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:24,120
I know what I got to do !

854
00:35:24,145 --> 00:35:25,581
I know what I got to do !

855
00:35:26,146 --> 00:35:28,991
Nobody comes in here and
talks to me like that.

856
00:35:29,252 --> 00:35:31,556
He said something about
Joe Don's parents.

857
00:35:31,557 --> 00:35:32,257
Making it right ?

858
00:35:32,381 --> 00:35:35,327
I don't know what he's going to do,
and frankly, I don't care.

859
00:35:36,777 --> 00:35:39,671
So why wouldn't you look
at the evidence again, Ray ?

860
00:35:40,889 --> 00:35:44,112
You seriously entertaining
reopening this case ?

861
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:47,849
Get the hell out of my house.

862
00:36:06,867 --> 00:36:08,076
Nick !

863
00:36:08,077 --> 00:36:09,177
Get in.

864
00:36:22,169 --> 00:36:24,200
Joe Don's parent'' house, huh ?

865
00:36:24,738 --> 00:36:26,949
Been out here what ?

866
00:36:27,074 --> 00:36:28,560
An hour ?

867
00:36:31,311 --> 00:36:33,446
Just trying to figure
out what to say.

868
00:36:35,516 --> 00:36:38,570
You had a busy 48 hours.

869
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:40,302
You had us all worried.

870
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,522
Have I been fired yet?

871
00:36:43,026 --> 00:36:45,591
Maybe the boss can
pull some strings.

872
00:36:46,493 --> 00:36:47,503
For both of us.

873
00:36:47,876 --> 00:36:48,753
You ?

874
00:36:48,878 --> 00:36:51,353
Considering I covered up a DUI.

875
00:36:54,001 --> 00:36:55,449
Sorry about that.

876
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,333
You're a good cop, Nick...

877
00:37:01,075 --> 00:37:02,826
but you need help.

878
00:37:04,181 --> 00:37:06,329
I saw my my ex-wife Julie.

879
00:37:07,904 --> 00:37:09,786
She's got two kids.

880
00:37:10,451 --> 00:37:13,195
I always thought that that'd be me.

881
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:14,898
No, it's never too late.

882
00:37:17,487 --> 00:37:19,228
I'm happy for her.

883
00:37:21,307 --> 00:37:22,705
Back when they caught this case,

884
00:37:22,830 --> 00:37:25,662
it's all I wanted was a kid,
a family.

885
00:37:27,311 --> 00:37:29,539
And then when I saw that
burnt-out bedroom...

886
00:37:30,371 --> 00:37:31,714
And the kids...

887
00:37:32,536 --> 00:37:33,341
Yeah.

888
00:37:33,466 --> 00:37:37,557
Yeah, I sat down on the box
across from this man,

889
00:37:37,582 --> 00:37:40,686
this father that had...
had burned his kids alive,

890
00:37:40,781 --> 00:37:43,548
and I couldn't believe
someone could do that.

891
00:37:46,434 --> 00:37:47,606
Did he ?

892
00:37:47,766 --> 00:37:49,446
I went at him day and night, Lil.

893
00:37:49,893 --> 00:37:52,072
I knew something
wasn't right in my gut.

894
00:37:53,060 --> 00:37:55,282
I kept looking for that
one thing in his story,

895
00:37:55,307 --> 00:37:58,139
that one slip that just lets you...

896
00:37:59,177 --> 00:38:00,553
...lets you know he's a liar.

897
00:38:00,678 --> 00:38:02,944
Just needed one slip.

898
00:38:03,733 --> 00:38:04,847
But he never did.

899
00:38:04,972 --> 00:38:08,150
I didn't need a statement
to get a conviction. I had everything.

900
00:38:08,275 --> 00:38:09,852
I was just so sure he'd done it.

901
00:38:09,877 --> 00:38:12,144
And you weren't the only one, Nick.

902
00:38:18,952 --> 00:38:20,903
Firemen call it the "beast."

903
00:38:22,878 --> 00:38:24,392
Flashover.

904
00:38:25,196 --> 00:38:27,302
It only got hotter
when he went outside,

905
00:38:27,427 --> 00:38:30,555
trying to find another
way back to get his kids.

906
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:33,993
- But he couldn't.
- I just couldn't get my head around that.

907
00:38:34,118 --> 00:38:37,003
What that was like ?
I thought for sure he'd set that fire,

908
00:38:37,658 --> 00:38:39,716
and he tried to tell me,

909
00:38:39,917 --> 00:38:41,417
and I couldn't hear it.

910
00:38:41,728 --> 00:38:42,948
He tried to tell you what ?

911
00:38:43,073 --> 00:38:44,953
That he wasn't a killer.

912
00:38:45,078 --> 00:38:46,614
He was just afraid.

913
00:38:46,784 --> 00:38:47,930
Afraid for his own life.

914
00:38:48,055 --> 00:38:49,433
And for that,

915
00:38:49,734 --> 00:38:51,334
I couldn't forgive him.

916
00:38:52,619 --> 00:38:54,396
It was you, Joe Don.

917
00:38:54,667 --> 00:38:56,124
You started that fire,

918
00:38:56,292 --> 00:38:57,599
you burned up those kids.

919
00:38:57,724 --> 00:39:00,002
No, I could never do that.

920
00:39:00,127 --> 00:39:02,321
I would never hurt them.
I loved my boys.

921
00:39:02,346 --> 00:39:04,697
Really ? Then how could you just
leave them in there to die ?

922
00:39:06,212 --> 00:39:09,244
I just... The fire,
it was everywhere.

923
00:39:09,369 --> 00:39:11,964
It was so hot. You have no idea.

924
00:39:12,089 --> 00:39:13,215
You're right, I don't.

925
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,303
You had plenty of time to go
in there and get them out.

926
00:39:15,428 --> 00:39:17,832
No, I thought I could, but...

927
00:39:18,733 --> 00:39:20,533
it happened so fast and...

928
00:39:21,014 --> 00:39:23,485
And then I was on fire.

929
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:27,374
<i>The fire, it was,
it was everywhere.</i>

930
00:39:27,866 --> 00:39:31,222
And the heat, my God...

931
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,463
Help me believe you.

932
00:39:33,464 --> 00:39:35,264
How did a father not go back
inside

933
00:39:35,331 --> 00:39:36,581
and get his own boys out ?!

934
00:39:37,355 --> 00:39:38,831
- I don't know.
- You see, a man,

935
00:39:39,085 --> 00:39:41,376
a man would do anything
to save his own.

936
00:39:42,444 --> 00:39:43,671
I tried.

937
00:39:48,894 --> 00:39:52,345
I really tried...

938
00:39:53,709 --> 00:39:55,114
I don't believe you.

939
00:39:55,191 --> 00:39:56,043
You're a liar.

940
00:39:56,168 --> 00:39:57,483
You're a damn liar.

941
00:39:57,570 --> 00:39:59,847
How could you just stand by
and let that happen?!

942
00:39:59,972 --> 00:40:02,020
Help me understand that.

943
00:40:03,493 --> 00:40:06,904
- How ?!
- I don't know, all right ?

944
00:40:07,557 --> 00:40:08,859
I just...

945
00:40:10,630 --> 00:40:11,865
couldn't.

946
00:40:12,827 --> 00:40:14,354
I don't know.

947
00:40:15,355 --> 00:40:19,355
<i>"The thin ice" by Pink Floyd.</i>

948
00:40:21,308 --> 00:40:24,076
I mistook cowardice for guilt.

949
00:40:24,339 --> 00:40:26,645
It's an honest mistake, Nick.

950
00:40:26,899 --> 00:40:28,791
One that can't be made right.

951
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:36,300
Well, look, we'll talk to the DA.

952
00:40:36,726 --> 00:40:39,144
We'll try to clear his name.

953
00:40:41,022 --> 00:40:42,022
Okay ?

954
00:40:46,333 --> 00:40:48,313
First, I gotta do this.

955
00:41:07,389 --> 00:41:09,321
Mr. and Mrs. Billingsley,
I'm Detective Vera.

956
00:41:09,384 --> 00:41:10,697
I know who you are.

957
00:41:12,511 --> 00:41:14,293
I'm sorry for your loss.

958
00:41:14,318 --> 00:41:15,789
What do you want ?

959
00:41:18,399 --> 00:41:20,128
There's been some new
evidence in the case,

960
00:41:20,253 --> 00:41:22,444
and I know it will never
bring your son back,

961
00:41:23,003 --> 00:41:25,471
but I want you to know I'm going
to do everything I can to clear his name.

962
00:41:36,650 --> 00:41:39,852
<i>"Wish You Were Here"
by Pink Floyd.</i>

963
00:41:43,488 --> 00:41:44,788
* So... *

964
00:41:45,589 --> 00:41:49,332
* So, so, you think you can tell *

965
00:41:50,533 --> 00:41:53,333
* Heaven from Hell *

966
00:41:54,066 --> 00:41:57,069
* Blue skies from pain *

967
00:41:58,603 --> 00:42:02,311
* Can you tell a green field *

968
00:42:02,712 --> 00:42:06,212
* From a cold steel rail ? *

969
00:42:06,945 --> 00:42:10,015
* A smile from a veil ? *

970
00:42:10,950 --> 00:42:14,386
* Do you think you can tell ? *

971
00:42:15,521 --> 00:42:18,494
* Did they get you to trade *

